Class ShopBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.wauz.wauzcore.menu.ShopBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    WauzInventory

    public class ShopBuilder
extends java.lang.Object
implements WauzInventory
    An inventory that can be used as menu or for other custom interaction mechanics. Builds an usable shop out of a shop config file.

      • open

        public static void open(org.bukkit.entity.Player player,
                        java.lang.String shopName)
        Opens the menu for the given player. Reads all buyable items out of a shop config file. If the shop is global, only global currencies will be shown, the other 8 slots can be buyable items. Otherwhise all currencies, aswell as repair and sell options are shown, allowing only 6 buyable items. Empty slots will be filled with "SOLD OUT" signs.
        Parameters:
        player - The player that should view the inventory.
        shopName - The name of the shop to load.
        See Also:
        ShopConfigurator.isShopGlobal(String), ShopConfigurator.getItemAmount(String, int)

      • selectMenuPoint

        public void selectMenuPoint(org.bukkit.event.inventory.InventoryClickEvent event)
        Checks if an event in this inventory was triggered by a player click. Cancels the event and initiates the corresponding buy, sell or repair event. On an anvil click items on the cursor are repaired, while they are sold on a barrier click. Unlike ammo items (arrows), physical items, can only be bought when there is inventory space left. Items cannot be bought, if the player doesn't have enough money.
        Specified by:
        selectMenuPoint in interface WauzInventory
        Parameters:
        event - The inventory click event.
        See Also:
        sell(Player, ItemStack, Boolean), repair(Player, ItemStack, Boolean), ItemUtils.fitsInInventory(Inventory, ItemStack), ItemUtils.isAmmoItem(ItemStack), PlayerConfigurator.setCharacterCurrency(Player, String, long), PlayerConfigurator.setArrowAmount(Player, String, int)

      • sell

        public static boolean sell(org.bukkit.entity.Player player,
                           org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack itemToSell,
                           java.lang.Boolean fromShop)
        Tries to sell the given item for the player. The item stack will either be sold for a random value per item or with bonus on attack / defense. Some items have a fixed sell value in lore, while bought items are worth nothing. TODO: Also refactor this, when implementing equipment builder.
        Parameters:
        player - The player who wants to sell the item.
        itemToSell - The item that should be sold.
        fromShop - If the selling was triggered from a shop menu.
        Returns:
        If the selling was successful.
        See Also:
        PlayerConfigurator.setCharacterCoins(Player, long), PlayerPassiveSkillConfigurator.getTradingFloat(Player), AchievementTracker.addProgress(Player, WauzAchievementType, double)

      • repair

        public static boolean repair(org.bukkit.entity.Player player,
                             org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack itemToRepair,
                             java.lang.Boolean fromShop)
        Tries to repair the given item for the player. Cannot repair items with no or max durability value. If the item is repaired in a shop menu, it will have a cost, equal to the lost durability.
        Parameters:
        player - The player who wants to repair the item.
        itemToRepair - The item that should be repaired.
        fromShop - If the repairing was triggered from a shop menu.
        Returns:
        If the repairing was successful.
        See Also:
        EquipmentUtils.getCurrentDurability(ItemStack), EquipmentUtils.getMaximumDurability(ItemStack), PlayerConfigurator.setCharacterCoins(Player, long), DurabilityCalculator.repairItem(Player, ItemStack)
